    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup for LawDog hinges on capitalizing on favorable matchups against mid-tier arms, headlined by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands the highest score of the day at 80.92. Facing Civale, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** benefits significantly from a high park factor and elite skill projection, cementing his role as the focal point of our offensive production. We also see high-ceiling value in **Jonathan Aranda** (66.61) and **Taylor Ward** (64.43). **Taylor Ward** is a particularly intriguing play today; despite facing a tough opponent in Fried, the combination of his leadoff spot, positive park factors, and a strong platoon edge against the southpaw elevates his daily efficiency score well into our \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nTactically, we are monitoring the bottom of our order closely. While **Masyn Winn** and **Wenceel Perez** both carry sub-50 scores, their inclusion is driven by the potential for stolen bases, a category we prioritize heavily. The decision to start **Wenceel Perez** over the bench was partially buoyed by the prospect of running on a slow pitcher delivery. Conversely, **Luis Arraez** represents our most difficult \"near-miss\" decision. He produced a 42.11, hovering just above our marginal threshold, but was ultimately benched because his profile lacks the elite sprint speed or high-volume counting stat potential needed to justify bumping higher-upside options like **Daulton Varsho** or **Matt Chapman** in today\u2019s specific matchup against Matz. \n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of our lower-tier starters. While **Geraldo Perdomo** (60.42) looks solid against Boyd, the wind blowing out adds a layer of variance that could either inflate his counting stats or complicate defensive efficiency. We are also wary of the risk surrounding **Jeremiah Jackson**, who sits at 44.94; while his elite hold on stolen bases is valuable, he is facing a challenging matchup against Fried. We are carrying **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, **Lawrence Butler**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** on the bench today, ready to rotate if the official lineups shift or if weather reports deteriorate across our slate.",
